It can also be used to hibernate and save work progress when power is turned off.zswapÂ :Â zswap is a kernel function that provides a compressed memory cache for swap pages. Pages that would otherwise be swapped to disk are compressed and stored in an in-memory storage pool. The difference compared with zram is that zswap works together with the swap device
column18: while zram is an in-memory swap device and does not require a backup swap device. If you want to hibernate
